  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2). The CFD solver employs three tunable configuration parameters: base mesh element size (target 0.15 mm near-wall), a power-law hemolysis exponent threshold (alpha = 0.765), and an iterative convergence tolerance (1e-5 for residuals). Validation activities were conducted at these chosen settings; however, the package does not formally pin or bind these values as deployment configuration, and the ContextOfUse places no constraint on the solver configuration used at deployment time.",
  "assuranceLevel": "Medium",
  "couName": "CPB use",
  "decision": "Accepted",
  "deviceClass": "Class II",
  "modelRiskLevel": 2,
