      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "Mesh convergence study — hemolysis index",
      "description": "Three mesh densities (coarse 0.35 mm, medium 0.25 mm, fine 0.15 mm base element size) were evaluated. Relative hemolysis index varied by less than 3% between medium and fine meshes. Validation results reported at the chosen fine-mesh setting of 0.15 mm base element size. No configuration record binds this mesh size for deployment use.",
      "quantityOfInterest": "Relative hemolysis index (RH)",
      "outcome": "RH convergence within 3% between medium and fine mesh; fine mesh adopted for subsequent validation runs."
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/validation/morrison-vr-02-experimental-comparison",
      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "Experimental comparison — 5-point flow-speed matrix",
      "description": "CFD predictions of normalized index of hemolysis (NIH) compared against in-vitro measurements across five flow-speed operating points (3–6 L/min; 2000–3500 RPM). Hemolysis power-law exponent threshold alpha set to 0.765 and iterative convergence tolerance set to 1e-5 for all simulation runs. Results at the chosen settings show agreement within experimental uncertainty bands (±15%). The specific values of alpha and convergence tolerance were selected by the analyst for this study; they are not documented as binding deployment parameters.",
      "quantityOfInterest": "Normalized index of hemolysis (NIH, mg/100 L)",
      "outcome": "CFD NIH predictions within ±15% of experimental values at all 5 operating points; worst-case operating condition identified at 3 L/min / 3500 RPM."
    },
    {
