      "rationale": "CFD NIH predictions compared against in-vitro measurements at 5 operating points. Maximum deviation 14.3%, mean signed error +4.1% (slight over-prediction). All points within the ±20% acceptance band. Comparison performed at the chosen solver settings (alpha = 0.765, convergence tolerance 1e-5, mesh 0.15 mm); these settings are not pinned in any binding configuration record for deployment. Required level 2 achieved at the settings used during validation."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "QoI (NIH, RH) are directly linked to clinical hemolysis risk and are accepted regulatory endpoints for CPB device submissions.",
      "rationale": "Normalized index of hemolysis (NIH) and relative hemolysis index (RH < 1) are FDA-recognized endpoints for CPB device hemolysis assessment. Both quantities are directly computable from CFD shear stress histories via the power-law hemolysis model. Relevance to clinical harm is well-established in literature. Required level 2 achieved."
    },
    {
